messageBody:
On Apr 19, 2013, at 2:31 PM, Michael Everson <everson@...> wrote:

 

Please see http://www.evertype.com/standards/iso10646/pdf/n4xxx-shavian-additions.pdf and please comment as soon as possible. Thank you.

Michael Everson * http://www.evertype.com/


In no particular order: 

- Disunified angled parentheses. Yay!
- Thanks for floating our collective concerns in (4). 
- Upside-down senior-Quickscript NO is the sort of thing that can (and should) be handled by a sufficiently fancy OpenType font, right?
- For 11a, did I miss the combining characters/composite sequences? I'm not sure if EXCITE and EXAM count as such. 

Thanks,
— Nathan
